hopobject.body: Best Site Good Work donde comprar misoprostol en venezuela When a customer uses a card, the retailer receives from his bank (the acquiring bank) the money less a "merchant service charge". A large part of this charge is determined by the interchange fee. The customer's bank (the issuing bank), in turn, pays the acquiring bank the money minus the "multilateral interchange fees" or MIF, after taking the full amount from the customer's bank account.
